Lovely dosas!

Visiting D.C. for spring break and felt like having indian food. I am from Dallas which has 100s of great indian restaurants. So I really had high expectations. Ordered palak paneer, rotis and veg uttapam. The restaurant is not open for dine-in due to COVID but they delivered order within 30 mins. The palak paneer was just like how I make it at home. Unlike other restaurants, this place had not used any cream in it. The ingredients used were very fresh and I could taste caramelized onions, fresh garlic and ginger in the palak paneer. The mix veg uttapam was also delicious. Rotis were soft and freshly prepared. I highly recommend this place if you are in mood for indian food.
Food was so good, I would say this one is amongst my top five!! Very clean and fast service as well Thank you
Didn’t care for the vedz burger

Disappointing given the current 4.9 rating, but not bad. I had the Vegetable Biryani, Paneer Vindaloo, naan, and samosas. The Biryani was the most disappointing, 2-stars; veggies were neither particularly fresh nor abundant. The Paneer Vindaloo had good spice and solid amount of potato and paneer, the flavor was okay; 3-stars. The naan was 1-star, maybe worst I've ever had. The samosas were okay.
So delicious :) I tried the gobi dosa and it was amazing, I can’t wait to go back and try more!! 10/10 would recommend, it was also fast and the people are friendly

Delicious food and a nice reminder that home food is never too far away, especially with the phool jhadu by the front. I've walked by this place many times and finally decided to try after my friends spoke so highly about it -- satisfying, delicious, and very reasonably priced. Also yummy freshly-squeezed juices! Will definitely be going back, a gem in Adams Morgan that we need to preserve, support local :)
So delicious! I called to pickup my order and it was ready to go. Their samosas and dosas are amazing and the burger was great considering I’m not vegan/vegetarian. Highly recommend :)
Creative: they don’t just leave everything to potatoes. Quick, affordable and friendly.
The very best. Great Dosas. Delicious curries. Excellent service. I ordered online and used curbside delivery. Very easy.
Delicious food!!😍😍
My favorite Vegan Stop
Very tasty food & staff's are very friendly..
Awesome tast...masala dosha superbbbb
Best Dosa in the city

Have walked by this hole in the wall many times, but hadn't had occasion to actually try it until today. It's great! Very reasonably prices for good portions, and it is quite good, especially at the price point. I liked the aloo palak in particular and will certainly back to try a dosa.

Fantastic experience all around! My brother, brother in-law, and I ordered a number of things off the menu and we couldn’t decide which dish we liked the best because they were all so good!  All dishes were well prepared for pickup and easily shareable. At the heart of the matter they serve warm comfort food, and as it gets chillier outside; we will be sure to frequent this stop.  The gentleman and the boy behind the curtain, and in the kitchen, were extremely pleasant and welcoming and left an overall great impression.  I would highly recommend this place!

Always excited to see an all veg Indian restaurant. Especially in DC!  Got samosas and gobi manchurian as an afternoon snack and both were really fresh and tasty dishes. Can’t wait to come back and try some more dishes. Also, order taker was very nice and answered my questions.

I didn’t know what a dosa was prior to eating here...but VEGZ has made me a huge dosa fan. As stated in the other reviews, this is a great spot for vegetarians, vegans, and gluten free folks. I also appreciate the fair pricing that seems to be increasingly rare in DC these days.  I enjoyed the spinach, spring and mysore masala dosas. Husband loved the veggie burger and the fries were the cherry on top! They reminded me of the best version of McDonald’s French fries and were served with a yummy mambo type sauce. We loved it so much that we brought our entire family dosas the following weekend and they agreed, VEGZ is the real deal!
Excellent food, underrated and hidden!
Amazing vegan food!

Food is delicious, but if you have allergies beware: GF and Vegan items are not labeled correctly! Food tasted good but be prepared to get sick like I did. I really wanted to like this place since it seemed to cater to those with food allergies/sensitivities, but their menu labeling is just plain dangerous. Seamless has items listed GF that are not. Both Vegz and delivery menus have items listed as Vegan that contain dairy. Not cool.
Pleasantly surprised at how good this was. Bravo, VEGZ. You gave a South Indian guy a reason to believe. Soul cleansing dosa a click away.

I ordered via DoorDash. The food arrived in just 30 minutes. For $11 you get a generous portion of dosa, a sauce and two dips. I ordered the Spinach Dosa and that was so delicious! I strongly recommend this place to those who are vegetarian/ vegan.
I just love their oprions!! Another good place for vegans.

This was, by far, one of the best local take-out experiences in the AdMo area.  With a group of five friends, every Friday during COVID, we have ordered out from various, highly rated restaurants in the DC area, to get a true sense of DC food. Many of those highly-rated, nodded-at restaurants provided less that expected food and service. This is not the case for VEGZ. Service was polite, professional, and knowledgeable, even after my multiple calls to clarify menu items to determine the best serving size for our group of six, hearty eaters. Online ordering was simple, and pick-up was effortless. Food was packed clearly, and easy to portion out. The quality of food, simply stating, was amazing! We were left talking about the meal for days afterwards - whereas many highly-acclaimed (Michelin and WaPo) restaurants barely left us talking about the food hours after the meal. And, since this is a review, as a meat lover, I never felt as though something was missing.  I am passing on the word about this gem! Thank you, VEGZ, for the beautiful meal and contributing to diversity of dining in our city.
Quality of food, taste very delicious. staff working there always smiling and friendly. Real authenticate Indian taste of the food I had. Keep up the jobs guys !!!!

Great customer service, amazing Vegan options - the Vegz Vegan Burger made out of potatoes was delicious. Actually all the items we got was fresh made & tasty. Cheap prices for bountiful portions & again the employees are uber friendly! Located across the street from the Marie Reed Tennis Courts.
Got dosas delivery and it was amazingly fresh and delicious. Very very recommended!

Fast, no frills, clean, and delicious! The staff were really friendly, and there was an amazing selection of vegetarian and vegan dishes. I got eggplant and my friend had fried okra. We split an order of fries. Everything was amazing! Lots of other things on the menu looked great, so I’ll definitely go back again. The prices were very reasonable, too.

The food is amazing. I'm not a fan of vegetables but the food was delicious, things I don't usually like I loved. It's small and clean,  overall I had a great dining expirence. Everything was fantastic!

VEGZ is so yummy! I went there yesterday for some vegan Indian food and was thrilled. The food was fast and delicious and the employees were so friendly. I actually tried to go back the next day again but it was Monday and they were closed 😂 but that should be a testament to how delicious the food was.
Very tasty! Great takeout dishes.
Its hard to find south Indian food around the area and this is so far the best restaurant! Had a great time in there and definitely will be going there often lol!
Had the black lentils with rice which were delicious! Staff were incredibly nice. Just visiting DC but now have an awesome vegan/vegetarian spot to return to!
An awesome place in Adams Morgan.Delicious food ,fresh carrot juice,reasonable price,few chat with owner he is so awesome. Definitely will come back with my family

We ordered hummus & pita, black lentils, garbanzo beans, eggplant, green savory dosa, and chapati bread. The hummus, black lentils, and dosa were my favorites but it was all delicious. We ordered for carry out and forgot to check our order before leaving. The cashier realized we forgot something and sprinted down the street and around to corner to catch up to us and give it to us- excellent customer service!
They have best samosas i have ever had. You definitely should try them.
The food was delicious and the service was good as well. Main complaint was the use of plastic cutlery and paper plates which cheapened the whole experience.

Best meal we’ve had in DC in a long time. The spicy coconut dosa and the soup that comes with it are both out of this world. The crispy spinach is just as good at Rasika’s but you get three times as much. I can’t wait to go back!
Uniquely delicious, friendly, and cozy.
This place has South Indian food that is normally very hard to find, specially idiyappam and uthappam. They also have other really good South Indian food, including dosas

Fantastic food and ambiance. The hummus and baked eggplant were out of this world, and the yellow lentils were delicious as well! We got an appetizer, 2 generous entrees, and naan, all for about $30. Would highly recommend!
Great food, better value. Will surely be returning
Delightful south Indian cuisine in Adams Morgan! It is hard to find a decent dosa in Washington DC. This is by far the best dosa place in the District.
We split a potato crepe, a spinach crepe, and some fries between 3 of us and were all full. The food tastes amazing and the staff are friendly. Will definitely go back.
Delicious, friendly, inexpensive.

Best quality Indian food tasted ever. A lot of good flavor Indian spices. Fresh juice with awesome friendly service. Clean public restrooms and dining area... must visit place in Adams Morgan to grab a bite....

Fast and gracious service.   Delicious food, also have fresh apple and carrot juice (juiced in store).  The dosas are delicious and the crackled baby spinach is also super tasty.  All the items in the menu are amazing.  They even have hummus!
Great food at great prices.  Dosas are the best in the city.  Baked eggplant is awesome.  And try fresh juices too! Highly recommended for everyone and  especially vegetarians.
Amazing food.  Comes out very fast and the employees are very helpful and nice. It's a cute little hole in the wall, 10/10 would recommend.  The food is super tasty and good pricing.
Omg the crepes and the dosas were amazing and delicious. Very contempt don't be fooled you will be satisfied with just 1 crepes. Worth all 5 stars!
the crepes are excellent
Great food great prices. Love chilly paneer
This place is amazing for Vegetarians. Thanks for serving such a high quality food with reasonable price.
Very unique flavored veggie patty...Indian flavors. They have inexpensive veggie burgers that come with good string fries. Fried potato samosas are great too.

Limited menu and DELICIOUS in taste!!!  You cannot go wrong with dosa, chilly paneer and home-made Gulab jamuns. Especially for dosa ask for extra crispy. Most of the food is prepared fresh right in front of you.  If you have been to Indian restaurants before, some items on the menu may not seem familiar; however, you may recognize some item when their Indian names are mentioned. For example, Potato pastry = Samosa, Spinach & cheese = Palak paneer, Vegetable Croquets = Malai Kofta and so on.  It is a family-run place so everyone is very friendly. Most likely it is the First Indian vegetarian/vegan restaurant in D.C.  Satisfy your craving of authentic Indian food.
Delish veg Indian food at great price! Owner and staff are lovely and hospitable!
VEGZ has amazing and authentic Indian food! Highly recommend. Their dosas with sambar are so delicious and you must the chilly paneer!
It's Indian. But fresher, great somosas.

THERE IS FINALLY A GOOD DOSA PLACE IN DC!!!!! I am so excited. This little spot has traditional dosas, and they're delicious. They're not the super trendy, mixed with gluten, weirdly soft, and utterly overdone hip dosas that cost $15 per order. Instead they feel authentic and legit - which means they're gluten free and vegan too! The sambar is also great. The owner and staff are all super friendly and helpful and fun to chat with. I think I'm in love.
Great vegetarian Indian food at an affordable price.
Amazing food (especially the rice crepe!) Great and friendly staff:) the amounts are more than enough and the place is very clean.
Great food. Specially Chilli Paneer. Also try Yogurt Mango. Veggie Burger was exactly like what we get in India...amazing
Excellent Indian food and great customer service! I had the potato rice crepe (which is gluten free!) and had enough for leftovers the next day. Awesome new addition to the neighborhood!
Tasty food, reasonably priced, and the guys who work here are really friendly.  I highly recommend!
Super delicious vegan food.  We’ve been here 3 times so far and tried some thing different each time and they all hit the spot.  Can’t wait to try the whole menu.
(Translated by Google) Great Masala Dosa and Paneer Makani.  (Original) Great Masala Dosa and Paneer Makani.

We tried masala dosa(crepe), vege burger . Both were good. Good sambar and chutneys. Sitting space is basic. They make the food in front of you. So its fresh. No parking here, you will be very lucky if you find parking here.

Perfect addition to the neighborhood. Delicious, quick, well-priced, nice owners, and relatively healthy. My two favorites are the chilly paneer and the cracked baby spinach but honestly, everything I've tried has been good. Keep up the amazing work!
One of the best dosa I ever had .
The dosa and channa masala were amazing! They have great veggies options and great customer service!!
Great food great place !! Amazing place in Adams Morgan! They have really good Indian crepes and vegan options on affordable price!

Delicious and quick eats. I am vegetarian with a partner who is allergic to dairy, tomatoes, and wheat. So, as you can imagine, it can be difficult to find restaurants for us both to enjoy. This place ticks all the boxes and is yummy! Good new local spot for me.
Customer service is perfect! Food was great. Will go back and recommend for authentic tasty dishes!
Really good for my first time here. Amazing customer service. Just come and try it out. That's it, you will come back.
Fantastic food with good prices.
Excellent vegan options.
Delicious, flavorful, affordable, vegetarian. What more do you want? Also, one of the only places in the city you can get a dosa!

Great Indian food with vegan and vegetarian focus and variety. I really liked the food and the price is very good. Friendly people who really cares about the happiness of their customers. I had a diner plate and one to go for my friend.

Stopped in for lunch after walking by so many times — I didn’t get the lunch deal, but I did have the peas and paneer “big plate” and it was delicious. Good serving size (enough to save for leftovers tomorrow) and also got some delicious naan. Small, cute place. Will be back!

Great dosas -- by far best in DC  So excited there are finally great dosas in DC! Light, crispy and tender dosa, super savory fillings, and tasty sambar. (They are far better than the limited current DC dosa options.) Biryani and its sauces also delicious. All very reasonably priced, and friendly owners. Can't wait to try more from the menu, but it will be hard to not just order more and more and more dosas.

Loved the masala (potato) dosa and the homemade veggie burger was awesome!  Recommend: This place is new, so needs some work on the wording of menu items and also some of the drink options. For example, would be great if the carrot juice was actually like a carrot-ginger-turmeric juice. Plain carrot juice is a little blah. Also, why isn’t there a water dispenser so that we don’t have to buy a plastic bottle item (there also isn’t a recycling bin if we’re forced to buy bottled).

An awesome vegan/vegetarian place in Adams Morgan! Really great food at an affordable price and serving portions are great! I got the dinner special which comes with a choice of 2 entrees (I got chickpea, and potato) with rice and a side of pita bread for only $7.99!  I love the homey-family atmosphere as you see the staff cook and prep your meals while you wait. Tell everyone you know who enjoys vegan/vegetarian food, because this place is a must-try.  Will definitely come back and try their other menu options. 😁

Amazing! We went on a Monday night and got the mango lassi, croquettes, red onion crepe, and paneer dish. It was so delicious and flavorful. Cozy, not fancy place - but we’re already planning how to work through their menu.
This is a nice addition to the neighborhood! It is all vegetarian and vegan Indian fast casual. Great lunch special at 799, and tasty pancakes / dosas. Pleasant and welcoming owners and staff!
